  …lauds Buhari for tackling nation’s challenges.  SEGUN AYINDE, ABEOKUTA  Ogun State Governor, Senator Ibikunle Amosun has called on Nigerians to ensure peaceful coexistence and unity among themselves for the development of the nation. Amosun made this known at the celebration of the 58th Independence Day anniversary held at M.K.O Abiola Stadium, Kuto, Abeokuta, the state capital. He however urged Nigerians not to allow division among themselves, saying that no nation could progress without unity. The governor who lauded President Muhammadu Buhari in the way and manner he tackled the challenges confronting the nation, charged Nigerians to continue to make sacrifices and always strive for peace and unity in the country. He said; “Democracy has come to stay, we should celebrate despite the challenges. I commend President Muhammadu Buhari in the way he has been combating the various challenges in the country.” “We must celebrate the 58th independent day and reexamine our commitment to the Nigeria project, work to deepen our democracy, seek something to unite than to divide us.” The governor also maintained that his administration would not deviate from the ‘Ogun standard’ in making the state  better than the way he met it, adding that the seven years of his government had been eventful. He said that his administration would not shy away from adequate security of lives and properties of the state citizens and education which the state is well known for, as well as ensuring to leave a better administrative system in the state before leaving the office by May next year. 